WEBVTT

00:12.053 --> 00:13.346
(panting)

00:13.888 --> 00:14.889
(exhales)

00:19.853 --> 00:21.271
-(breaks wind)
-(groans)

00:24.315 --> 00:26.693
(rustling)

00:55.346 --> 00:56.347
(grunts)

00:58.224 --> 01:00.226
(mutters)
(hums)

01:04.064 --> 01:05.148
(grunting)

01:05.607 --> 01:07.192
(knocking on door)

01:09.694 --> 01:11.738
Sir, could you step out
of the stall, please?

01:15.450 --> 01:17.619
Sir, can I see some
identification, please?

01:17.702 --> 01:19.162
It's a courthouse. Denny Crane.

01:19.537 --> 01:21.998
I don't need to identify myself
in a courthouse.

01:22.082 --> 01:23.249
Please place your hands
behind your back, sir.

01:23.333 --> 01:24.459
Why?

01:24.542 --> 01:25.919
Sir, you are under arrest
for solicitation.

01:26.002 --> 01:26.836
What?

01:26.920 --> 01:28.338
-You have the right to remain silent.
-Solicit--

01:28.421 --> 01:29.547
Anything you say
can and will be used against you...

01:29.631 --> 01:30.965
-Who the hell did I solicit?
-...in a court of law.

01:31.049 --> 01:32.592
You have the right to an attorney.

01:32.675 --> 01:34.636
Sir, please put your hands
behind your back now.

01:34.719 --> 01:36.137
-Alan.
-All right. That's it.

01:36.221 --> 01:37.055
Get him down on the floor.

01:37.138 --> 01:38.973
Wait a minute! Hey. Wait! (grunts)

01:39.057 --> 01:40.809
Al... Alan!

01:41.267 --> 01:42.727
Alan! Pick up, will you?

01:43.269 --> 01:45.355
Alan! Pick up!

01:45.438 --> 01:46.523
(theme music playing)

01:46.606 --> 01:49.067
Alan! Alan!

01:49.150 --> 01:50.527
<i>♪ Uh-huh ♪</i>

01:53.488 --> 01:54.739
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

01:56.324 --> 01:57.826
<i>♪ Come on ♪</i>

02:01.204 --> 02:03.248
<i>♪ Come on, all right ♪</i>

02:03.331 --> 02:04.249
<i>♪ Well, yeah ♪</i>

02:06.417 --> 02:07.585
<i>♪ Well, yeah ♪</i>

02:13.466 --> 02:15.385
<i>♪ Outlaw ♪</i>

02:22.142 --> 02:24.644
WHISTLER: He did all the known signals
for solicitation.

02:24.727 --> 02:26.354
In fact, he was quite methodical about it.

02:26.437 --> 02:27.814
-He's full of crap.
-Denny.

02:27.897 --> 02:29.649
Well, so was I, but I was constipated.

02:29.732 --> 02:32.026
What known signals?

02:32.110 --> 02:34.154
Well, first he came in,
looked under the stall doors.

02:34.237 --> 02:36.823
Then he entered a stall
next to an occupied one.

02:36.906 --> 02:38.366
He slid his briefcase to the front,

02:38.449 --> 02:40.827
making his feet visible
to the adjacent occupant.

02:40.910 --> 02:43.705
-Oh, please. I--
-He then moved his foot over.

02:43.788 --> 02:45.498
Then he began to hum quietly.

02:45.582 --> 02:48.501
Then he tapped his foot
four times, up and down.

02:48.585 --> 02:50.545
-Look, now first, we--
-Denny.

02:50.628 --> 02:52.547
Sir, look.
There's really no point denying this.

02:53.381 --> 02:55.133
Unless you consider innocence a point.

02:55.216 --> 02:57.343
Would that be a point worth considering?

02:57.427 --> 02:59.762
These are well-known solicitation signals.

02:59.846 --> 03:01.389
-(scoffs)
-You didn't even go to the bathroom,

03:01.472 --> 03:02.348
by the way, did you?

03:02.432 --> 03:05.351
Because I was constipated.
Did we not go over this?

03:05.435 --> 03:07.896
My suggestion is that
you make this go away quietly.

03:08.771 --> 03:10.648
Bribe. I knew it.

03:10.732 --> 03:12.567
I'm not suggesting a bribe.

03:12.650 --> 03:15.195
My recommendation is that you plead guilty
to disorderly conduct.

03:15.278 --> 03:17.697
(chuckles)
He's not gonna plead guilty to anything.

03:17.780 --> 03:19.908
You really want these charges
to be made public?

03:20.366 --> 03:23.411
This sounds an awful lot like extortion,
Officer Whistler.

03:23.494 --> 03:25.663
It's not extortion.
I'm just saying your choice.

03:25.747 --> 03:27.832
Disorderly conduct and a small fine

03:27.916 --> 03:30.877
or a public trial
for solicitation to have gay sex.

03:31.419 --> 03:32.253
Trial.

03:32.587 --> 03:35.840
-Wait, wait, wait.
-Denny. Trial.

03:37.467 --> 03:38.343
(exclaiming)

03:42.096 --> 03:44.682
-(elevator bell dings)
-Why are you angry at me?

03:44.766 --> 03:46.726
Because I could've made this thing
go away quietly.

03:46.809 --> 03:49.270
-You're making it into a cause.
-I am not, Denny.

03:49.354 --> 03:51.731
You're being Larry Craig-d here,
and it isn't fair.

03:51.814 --> 03:53.399
But with a public trial?

03:53.483 --> 03:55.735
It's one thing for people
to think I've got Alzheimer's

03:55.818 --> 03:58.821
or I've lost my mind,
but for them to think I'm gay?

03:58.905 --> 04:03.409
Denny, for God's sake, you cannot
plead guilty. It's a ridiculous charge.

04:03.493 --> 04:04.619
The police had no bus--

04:06.537 --> 04:07.705
What's going on?

04:08.289 --> 04:10.541
Uh, Denny had a little
misunderstanding this morning.

04:12.210 --> 04:16.089
In an effort to relieve
some mild constipation,

04:16.673 --> 04:18.675
he unwittingly offered
to be a whistle-blower

04:18.758 --> 04:20.343
for an undercover police officer.

04:22.512 --> 04:24.973
-It happens.
-He's being arraigned this afternoon.

04:25.056 --> 04:26.766
I'm moving for an immediate dismissal.

04:41.614 --> 04:45.159
The Battleship. As I live and breathe.

04:45.243 --> 04:48.705
Wow. You get more and more beautiful.

04:49.998 --> 04:51.207
Who's suing you now?

04:52.166 --> 04:53.710
I take it you haven't heard.

04:54.919 --> 04:55.753
Uh-oh.

04:56.296 --> 04:58.881
-I got fired, Shirl.
-What?

04:58.965 --> 05:01.634
As of now, you're looking at
an unemployed shock jock.

05:02.802 --> 05:03.928
What did you say?

05:04.012 --> 05:05.138
Oh, nothing too bad,

05:05.221 --> 05:08.224
-but as far as the station's concerned--
-What did you say?

05:08.308 --> 05:10.310
Oh, something like,
"Old people should die."

05:11.352 --> 05:12.812
You said that on the air?

05:12.895 --> 05:14.480
Oh, come on.
It's the radio, for God sakes.

05:14.564 --> 05:18.276
If you can't be vulgar there...
Free speech. Rah!

05:20.653 --> 05:21.821
Look, seriously, Shirley...

05:23.823 --> 05:25.616
I'm not a young man.

05:25.700 --> 05:28.870
If I lose this gig,
I may not get another one.

05:29.412 --> 05:30.371
I need to fight this.

05:30.830 --> 05:31.664
(sighs)

05:32.623 --> 05:34.584
"Old people should die."

05:35.293 --> 05:37.712
Free speech. Rah.

05:37.795 --> 05:39.255
(chuckles)

05:39.339 --> 05:40.173
Rah.

05:41.215 --> 05:43.509
-Why would Paul want to see us?
-Obviously Sack told him.

05:43.593 --> 05:44.927
Maybe Paul's gay.

05:45.011 --> 05:46.512
God, why can't I have that?

05:51.351 --> 05:54.812
Ah. I see somebody has run
to the principal's office.

05:55.021 --> 05:58.816
-Hello, Alan. Denny, how are you?
-Not gay.

05:59.609 --> 06:00.443
Yes.

06:01.152 --> 06:04.072
Carl has shared with me the latest.

06:04.405 --> 06:06.157
I'm told there's a chance
of making this go away

06:06.240 --> 06:08.326
with a disorderly conduct plea.

06:08.409 --> 06:09.952
That was rejected.

06:10.870 --> 06:12.205
May I ask why?

06:13.623 --> 06:14.832
He's innocent, Paul.

06:14.916 --> 06:18.878
Alan, you know and I know
that the charges alone--

06:18.961 --> 06:20.713
Denny's been charged with crimes before.

06:20.797 --> 06:23.674
This one leaves its own special tarnish.

06:23.758 --> 06:26.594
Even an outright acquittal
won't amount to exoneration.

06:26.677 --> 06:29.055
We need to dispose of this
as quietly as possible.

06:29.138 --> 06:30.681
(laughs) This is ridiculous.

06:30.765 --> 06:33.601
He's being railroaded
by some overzealous cop

06:33.684 --> 06:35.269
who's staking out a bathroom.

06:35.353 --> 06:38.022
I don't know
if it's more offensive or silly.

06:38.689 --> 06:40.525
Denny, may I speak with you in private?

06:42.318 --> 06:43.945
Let's go, Al.
Let's give them some special time.

06:44.737 --> 06:46.989
If you care to leave, Carl, please do so,

06:47.073 --> 06:49.117
but, Paul, anything you have to say
to Denny, you can say--

06:49.200 --> 06:51.452
With all due respect to your friendship,

06:51.994 --> 06:54.288
Denny and I go back almost 40 years.

06:54.747 --> 06:57.083
Wow. You really are old, Paul.

06:59.627 --> 07:02.588
Go ahead, Alan.
Bond with Carl for a second.

07:02.672 --> 07:03.965
No sleepovers.

07:10.179 --> 07:11.013
(exhales)

07:12.473 --> 07:15.643
Carl Sack has the job
of worrying about the firm.

07:15.726 --> 07:18.604
I was happy to pass that baton.

07:20.815 --> 07:23.317
I'm concerned about you.

07:24.318 --> 07:28.531
Look, I see Alan all poised here
to climb on his soapbox,

07:29.073 --> 07:30.366
but at whose expense?

07:31.117 --> 07:32.368
If I plead to disorderly,

07:32.452 --> 07:34.537
the papers'll make straw
out of that as well.

07:34.871 --> 07:35.746
Denny...

07:36.873 --> 07:40.209
your grip on your position here
as senior partner,

07:40.293 --> 07:43.463
I know you know is a little tenuous.

07:43.546 --> 07:45.923
This may be all the managing partners need

07:46.007 --> 07:48.217
to finally take your name off the door.

07:48.301 --> 07:51.471
-Which is why I need to be vindicated.
-And should you lose?

07:52.388 --> 07:53.222
Paul...

07:55.725 --> 07:59.187
right or wrong, I need to go out as...

08:00.688 --> 08:01.731
Denny Crane.

08:03.816 --> 08:05.943
I don't want my legacy to... (sighs)

08:11.574 --> 08:13.826
It's worth risking my job...

08:15.119 --> 08:16.370
to save my reputation.

08:18.623 --> 08:20.500
I'm afraid you may lose both.

08:21.417 --> 08:22.251
Not if we win.

08:25.379 --> 08:26.214
All or nothing.

08:28.424 --> 08:29.759
You and I used to say that all the time.

08:32.887 --> 08:33.721
Remember?

08:39.602 --> 08:41.562
(indistinct murmuring)

08:41.646 --> 08:43.689
Why a judge and not a jury?

08:43.773 --> 08:45.525
Juries can't give equitable relief.

08:45.608 --> 08:48.277
Plus, they don't especially
enjoy being summoned

08:48.361 --> 08:50.446
for something trivial
like First Amendment.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.281
BETHANY: Well, well, well.

08:54.992 --> 08:57.245
-Bethany.
-Shirley.

08:57.328 --> 08:59.747
Wow. You've let yourself go.

09:00.498 --> 09:01.916
I find that refreshing.

09:01.999 --> 09:06.295
It's so nice to see an elderly person
who's not afraid to look her age.

09:06.379 --> 09:09.173
Yes, well, vanity can be
quite the beast, I suppose.

09:09.757 --> 09:13.052
-I see you're wearing heels.
-Dwarf jokes. Classy.

09:13.344 --> 09:15.179
-MALE BAILIFF: All rise.
-(clears throat)

09:16.722 --> 09:19.892
In re: <i>Binder vs. WWEN Boston.</i>

09:19.976 --> 09:22.103
Judge Victoria Thomson presiding.

09:22.395 --> 09:23.521
This court is in session.

09:24.021 --> 09:26.190
Good morning, Your Honor.
Shirley Schmidt for the plaintiff.

09:26.274 --> 09:28.651
I'm not interested.
Who's the station manager?

09:28.734 --> 09:29.944
Uh, I am, Your Honor.

09:30.027 --> 09:34.991
And my name is Bethany Horowitz.
I represent WWEN.

09:35.074 --> 09:36.659
And why are you staring?

09:37.368 --> 09:39.870
'Cause I almost bought that same outfit.

09:39.954 --> 09:41.664
Sit your itty-bitty self down.

09:41.747 --> 09:43.749
Mr. Flanders, in the witness chair now.

09:44.458 --> 09:45.710
-Move it.
-BETHANY: But wait a second.

09:45.793 --> 09:48.462
-They're the ones suing.
-JUDGE THOMSON: I know that.

09:48.546 --> 09:50.840
I want to hear from him. Now.

09:57.471 --> 09:59.724
<i>Denny Crane in a men's room.</i>

10:00.057 --> 10:01.601
<i>Don't you just love that?</i>

10:01.684 --> 10:04.186
<i>Another "family values" advocate</i>

10:04.270 --> 10:07.189
<i>looking to use another man's private part</i>

10:07.273 --> 10:09.400
<i>-as a sippy cup.</i>
-Oh, God.

10:09.483 --> 10:10.943
<i>Time to go to church now, Denny?</i>

10:11.027 --> 10:13.821
<i>Time to get in touch with God?</i>
<i>Off to rehab we go?</i>

10:13.904 --> 10:16.782
<i>Doesn't it just make you want to snorkel</i>
<i>in your mother's vomit?</i>

10:16.866 --> 10:17.700
(turns off TV)

10:19.076 --> 10:21.495
I can't take it. The press is into it.

10:21.579 --> 10:23.164
I'm gay fodder. I can't take it.

10:23.581 --> 10:25.082
Come on, Denny. Let's just get to court.

10:25.166 --> 10:27.793
That woman, of all people,
knows I am straight.

10:27.877 --> 10:29.670
She told me
it was the best sex she ever had

10:29.754 --> 10:31.088
since her brother in ninth grade.

10:31.172 --> 10:32.089
She told me.

10:32.715 --> 10:34.216
We go for immediate dismissal.

10:34.300 --> 10:36.552
-None of this continuance crap.
-Immediate.

10:39.472 --> 10:41.891
-Lorraine.
-Alan. Denny.

10:42.850 --> 10:45.353
Would you be riding
on the elevator with us?

10:45.436 --> 10:46.687
Think you can handle it, Denny?

10:47.229 --> 10:49.398
(laughs) Well, maybe not.

10:50.066 --> 10:53.778
I don't know whether you've heard
about my, uh, predicament.

10:53.861 --> 10:55.946
I heard that you were humming
in the men's room.

10:56.489 --> 10:57.865
-That predicament?
-Yeah. Yeah.

10:58.532 --> 11:00.368
Rumors are ugly things, Lorraine.

11:01.577 --> 11:04.288
-I'll bet there's some about you.
-I wouldn't know.

11:04.372 --> 11:07.166
Neither would I. (chuckles)

11:07.249 --> 11:11.587
There are security cameras
on these elevators.

11:11.671 --> 11:15.216
If I were to have sex
on one with a-a woman,

11:15.299 --> 11:19.679
that would dispel
the horrible rumor that I, um...

11:19.762 --> 11:21.347
Uh, you know, uh...

11:21.430 --> 11:23.891
-Like to hum in men's rooms?
-Would you mind?

11:23.974 --> 11:27.269
Not at all, Denny.
But I am involved, so I can't.

11:27.353 --> 11:30.523
-Please. It's an emergency.
-Perhaps you should call 999.

11:30.606 --> 11:31.565
(elevator bell dings)

11:34.694 --> 11:36.362
-What's his name?
-I'm sorry?

11:36.445 --> 11:37.947
Uh, the boyfriend. What's his name?

11:41.992 --> 11:43.953
-Were we meant to get on that?
-(groans)

11:54.588 --> 11:56.382
-Hey, Lorraine.
-Katie.

11:57.883 --> 11:59.885
How are you liking working here so far,

11:59.969 --> 12:02.805
aside from the misogynistic
bits and pieces?

12:02.888 --> 12:05.933
Oh, it's fine.
Personally, I enjoy being objectified.

12:06.016 --> 12:09.228
It's a wonderful prophylactic
if one doesn't care to be really known.

12:09.311 --> 12:10.855
(chuckles) I suppose.

12:11.981 --> 12:13.566
Somehow I feel I know you.

12:13.649 --> 12:16.569
Have we met before Crane, Poole &amp; Schmidt?

12:16.652 --> 12:17.486
I don't believe we have.

12:18.571 --> 12:19.405
Odd.

12:19.905 --> 12:21.031
Have you ever spent time in England?

12:21.115 --> 12:23.534
I haven't actually,
though I've always wanted to go.

12:25.035 --> 12:26.078
I just thought perhaps...

12:27.121 --> 12:30.249
When Denny said earlier he had
an emergency, you said, "Call 999."

12:31.041 --> 12:32.585
It's 911 actually.

12:32.668 --> 12:34.587
Of course it is. I said 999?

12:34.962 --> 12:38.174
Yes, which coincidentally
is the number one calls for an emergency

12:38.257 --> 12:39.091
in England.

12:39.592 --> 12:40.426
Hmm.

12:42.052 --> 12:44.513
-I guess that is a coincidence.
-Yes.

12:48.476 --> 12:50.895
Bye, Katie.
Hope the rest of your day goes well.

12:51.395 --> 12:52.229
You, too.

13:01.572 --> 13:03.365
Look, it's all about sales.

13:03.699 --> 13:07.244
Here we're faced with advertiser pullout,
a boycott by listeners.

13:07.328 --> 13:09.455
But he's a shock jock.
This is what he does.

13:09.538 --> 13:12.124
FLANDERS:
Yes, and if he makes money for us, fine.

13:12.208 --> 13:14.251
If he doesn't... (clicks tongue)
he goes.

13:14.335 --> 13:16.170
(scoffs) It's nothing personal here.

13:16.253 --> 13:19.006
He's been saying outrageous things
for 25 years.

13:19.089 --> 13:22.426
Yes, and a lot of people
have been listening to him for 25 years.

13:22.510 --> 13:25.513
-BETHANY: So, what's changed?
-Those listeners are old now.

13:25.596 --> 13:30.351
If he wants to put down Blacks,
or Jews or Episcopalians, fine.

13:30.434 --> 13:32.520
But our demographic is baby boomers.

13:32.603 --> 13:35.773
Insulting old people,
it affects our bottom line.

13:35.856 --> 13:37.066
It's a no-can-do.

13:37.900 --> 13:39.860
So, you admit that what he said

13:39.944 --> 13:42.238
was in the context of social commentary?

13:43.155 --> 13:46.283
-So what?
-So what? You're primarily a news station.

13:46.367 --> 13:50.162
No. We're primarily a profit center,
like every other news station.

13:51.163 --> 13:54.500
You had Ann Coulter on the show
last week as a guest.

13:55.042 --> 13:57.044
This is a woman
who referred to John Edwards

13:57.127 --> 13:59.547
using the homosexual "F" word.

13:59.630 --> 14:02.174
(chuckling)
No one takes Ann Coulter seriously.

14:02.591 --> 14:03.634
She's a joke.

14:03.717 --> 14:07.346
Since Bob is actually respected
for his political commentary...

14:08.305 --> 14:10.140
his remarks are more dangerous.

14:10.599 --> 14:13.602
You don't see a problem
firing a political commentator

14:13.686 --> 14:15.271
for making a political comment?

14:16.313 --> 14:17.356
Not really.

14:19.692 --> 14:20.526
Huh.

14:21.110 --> 14:25.781
Case number 66266.
<i>The Commonwealth versus Denny Crane.</i>

14:25.865 --> 14:28.117
Alan Shore appearing for Mr. Crane.

14:28.200 --> 14:30.911
I would ask that this arraignment
be quashed immediately.

14:30.995 --> 14:33.956
-You cannot quash an arraignment.
-But you can, Your Honor,

14:34.039 --> 14:36.083
and you should here,
because if you look at the facts,

14:36.166 --> 14:37.793
you'll see that even as alleged,

14:37.877 --> 14:39.712
they don't support
the charges being filed.

14:39.795 --> 14:40.880
No money ever changed hands.

14:40.963 --> 14:43.007
You don't have to go that far.
It's an inchoate crime.

14:43.090 --> 14:45.926
Suppose he just hit on another man
he found attractive?

14:46.010 --> 14:47.803
-Oh, my God.
-ALAN: Are you saying it's a crime

14:47.887 --> 14:49.555
for one man to propose sex to another?

14:49.638 --> 14:51.265
In some states, it probably is.

14:51.348 --> 14:54.268
But this is Massachusetts,
the home of Mitt Romney,

14:54.351 --> 14:56.604
a man who was once okay with gay unions.

14:57.271 --> 14:59.440
Though he's not okay with them now.

14:59.523 --> 15:02.151
-Let's all be clear on that.
-(gavel pounds)

15:02.651 --> 15:04.486
I'll not have you attacking my governor.

15:04.570 --> 15:06.447
Judge, you shouldn't even be on this case.

15:06.530 --> 15:09.033
If you'll remember,
I once defended you on a subject

15:09.116 --> 15:10.826
very near and dear to this one.

15:11.452 --> 15:13.913
I can be impartial. And I shall be.

15:13.996 --> 15:15.789
And you cannot quash an arraignment.

15:16.373 --> 15:18.709
If you want to try to kick it
after charges are filed--

15:18.792 --> 15:20.336
And that's Mr. Crane's choice?

15:20.419 --> 15:22.171
To plead out or face public ridicule?

15:22.254 --> 15:24.256
Have you noticed all the cameras,
by the way?

15:24.340 --> 15:25.925
It's extortion. This is a witch hunt.

15:26.008 --> 15:28.093
The DA's office
probably targeted Mr. Crane

15:28.177 --> 15:29.470
because of all the bad blood between--

15:29.553 --> 15:31.639
This is the United States of America!

15:31.722 --> 15:35.059
Our system of justice
does not dictate to district attorneys

15:35.142 --> 15:37.978
