31:57.498 --> 31:59.375
So, let me see.

32:01.669 --> 32:07.008
All right, we've got 29 current
or recent members of Congress

32:07.091 --> 32:08.801
accused of spousal abuse.

32:08.885 --> 32:11.679
Twenty-seven have been arrested
for driving under the influence.

32:11.763 --> 32:14.974
Nineteen current or recent members
accused of writing bad checks.

32:15.058 --> 32:18.353
Fourteen have drug-related arrests.
Eight busted for shoplifting.

32:18.436 --> 32:21.105
Seven for fraud.
Four for theft. Three for assault.

32:21.189 --> 32:23.524
But Larry Craig's the one
they simply must broom

32:23.608 --> 32:25.234
for tapping his foot in a men's room.

32:25.318 --> 32:28.404
And why are we paying the police
to tap back?

32:28.488 --> 32:30.406
With all this terror business,

32:30.490 --> 32:33.034
and these security crises
going on in airports,

32:33.117 --> 32:34.994
why are the police across the country

32:35.078 --> 32:37.038
manning bathroom stalls to play footsie?

32:38.247 --> 32:41.960
Mr. Shore, I shall ask you
to confine yourself to this case.

32:42.043 --> 32:45.964
I'm talking about this case.
Homophobia has run amok, Judge.

32:46.047 --> 32:49.258
It's the reason we're all gathered here,
and it's preposterous.

32:49.342 --> 32:52.470
We're actually sitting in a courtroom
wasting tax dollars

32:52.553 --> 32:55.181
because my client had gas,
he was constipated.

32:55.264 --> 32:57.934
He went to remedy his problem
in a bathroom, imagine that,

32:58.017 --> 33:00.728
where lo and behold,
three undercover police officers

33:00.812 --> 33:04.023
were lurking, waiting to interpret
a tapping foot as a call for gay sex.

33:05.191 --> 33:08.861
Now... maybe Larry Craig
deserved his fate.

33:08.945 --> 33:10.863
He was thrown in front of the very bus
he helped to build.

33:10.947 --> 33:13.116
But Denny Crane doesn't deserve this.

33:13.199 --> 33:14.701
All he was trying to do was take a crap.

33:14.784 --> 33:16.202
(scattered murmuring)

33:23.418 --> 33:26.462
And even if one were
to go there looking for sex,

33:26.546 --> 33:27.964
there's no law against that.

33:28.047 --> 33:31.050
The crime is soliciting for a fee.

33:31.134 --> 33:34.095
This complaint doesn't even allege
that any money was involved.

33:34.846 --> 33:37.223
As my Great-aunt Gert used to say,

33:37.306 --> 33:39.892
"This smells funny,
and I'm not going to eat it."

33:52.864 --> 33:55.450
The First Amendment
applies to state action only.

33:55.533 --> 33:57.368
Not private companies.

33:57.452 --> 34:01.831
If a government punishes Mr. Binder
for saying what he did, that's censorship.

34:01.914 --> 34:05.918
When a private business does so,
it's editorial control.

34:06.502 --> 34:08.588
-This isn't going well.
-You say something, Miss Schmidt?

34:09.088 --> 34:11.674
If I did,
I'm sure it wasn't important, Your Honor.

34:12.508 --> 34:14.886
-However...
-There's the magic word.

34:14.969 --> 34:18.973
...corporations have become
the biggest infringers of free expression.

34:19.057 --> 34:20.516
It's been going on for years.

34:20.600 --> 34:22.477
Starting with cigarette companies

34:22.560 --> 34:24.395
who pull their advertising dollars

34:24.479 --> 34:27.774
from any publication
that runs an article on cancer.

34:28.191 --> 34:32.403
Beyond that, corporations
are using something called SLAPP suits

34:32.487 --> 34:34.030
to chill free speech.

34:34.113 --> 34:39.077
So, when it comes to truth
in this country, the fix is in.

34:39.619 --> 34:41.537
As for talk-show hosts,

34:41.621 --> 34:44.624
the public gets the opinion
the sponsors pay for.

34:44.707 --> 34:46.918
Your Honor, this is truly riveting.

34:47.001 --> 34:49.462
But can you just give us the ruling?

34:49.545 --> 34:51.172
Dwarves have limited life spans.

34:51.506 --> 34:54.550
Judgment for the petitioner.
That work for you?

34:56.010 --> 34:57.553
Are you on drugs?

34:57.637 --> 34:59.472
He was hired to be a provocateur.

34:59.931 --> 35:02.558
He said inflammatory things before.

35:02.642 --> 35:05.478
He was championed
by the station for doing so.

35:05.561 --> 35:09.607
I'm ruling in favor of the plaintiff
on an estoppel theory.

35:10.983 --> 35:12.819
Please don't take this personal,
pip-squeak.

35:14.821 --> 35:16.280
I want that on the record.

35:16.781 --> 35:20.284
You know, that robe doesn't give you
the authority or the right

35:20.368 --> 35:24.080
to demean me for my size,
you barrage balloon.

35:26.124 --> 35:28.918
Go ahead. What are you gonna do?

35:33.256 --> 35:35.466
-(door opens)
-(gate buzzing)

35:36.384 --> 35:37.218
(door closes)

35:42.014 --> 35:42.849
Bethany?

35:48.146 --> 35:50.857
That cannon remark
was really below the belt.

35:52.984 --> 35:53.818
I'm sorry.

35:55.653 --> 35:57.780
It wasn't my intent to...

35:58.865 --> 36:00.825
well, stoop to your level.

36:00.908 --> 36:02.743
And please don't take that the wrong way.

36:03.744 --> 36:04.579
It's just...

36:06.122 --> 36:10.168
you seem to push my buttons
for whatever reason.

36:11.210 --> 36:12.545
Not many people can do that.

36:13.838 --> 36:16.507
Is it because I was with Denny
and you still love him?

36:17.216 --> 36:20.178
It could be many things, but not that.

36:21.512 --> 36:25.057
The truth is, I bet... I could like you.

36:27.476 --> 36:29.645
Okay, not a chance.

36:30.646 --> 36:33.441
But I do tip my hat to you, Bethany.

36:35.067 --> 36:36.861
You really are something.

36:38.404 --> 36:39.238
Thank you.

36:42.074 --> 36:44.869
Well, have a good night.

36:45.912 --> 36:47.205
Until we meet again.

36:48.080 --> 36:50.333
Yes. Until.

37:07.308 --> 37:09.101
-A fatwa?
-Shh!

37:09.185 --> 37:11.229
Some Pakistani put a hit on her?

37:12.480 --> 37:15.274
That's what she said.
I have heard of these honor killings.

37:16.442 --> 37:18.110
-A fatwa?
-Keep your voice down.

37:18.194 --> 37:20.363
-She asked me to keep her confidence.
-I'm not keeping it.

37:20.446 --> 37:23.157
-Whitney.
-Suppose her ex-husband shows up here?

37:23.241 --> 37:25.201
I'm not going down in some fatwa.

37:25.284 --> 37:26.118
(knocking on door)

37:28.412 --> 37:29.413
Hello.

37:29.705 --> 37:30.831
-(door closes)
-Hello.

37:31.249 --> 37:32.083
How's it going?

37:32.500 --> 37:33.626
(sighing)

37:34.627 --> 37:36.128
-What's going on?
-WHITNEY: Oh, nothing.

37:36.212 --> 37:38.965
Just discussing the Patriots
and Red Sox...

37:39.048 --> 37:39.924
and fatwas.

37:43.302 --> 37:44.303
I'm disappointed.

37:44.804 --> 37:48.182
You're disappointed?
You put us all at risk, girl.

37:48.266 --> 37:50.810
What if your ex-Pakistani
blows up the building, hmm?

37:50.893 --> 37:53.229
That would really disappoint me.

37:53.312 --> 37:55.314
In fact, we'd all go to pieces.

37:58.067 --> 37:59.777
(in British accent)
I can't stop you revealing my secret,

37:59.860 --> 38:01.070
if that's what you choose to do,

38:01.153 --> 38:03.072
but you will jeopardize my life.

38:14.500 --> 38:15.459
A fatwa?

38:28.097 --> 38:30.725
Can you imagine,
of all the times I've beaten the rap,

38:31.517 --> 38:33.936
to be convicted of public gayness?

38:34.270 --> 38:36.439
I'll be forced to un-register
as a Republican.

38:36.522 --> 38:39.150
Republicans would have no problem
with you being gay, Denny,

38:39.233 --> 38:41.569
so long as you continue
to persecute homosexuals.

38:41.652 --> 38:43.070
I hope you're right.

38:43.821 --> 38:47.074
Madam Foreperson,
the jury's verdict is unanimous?

38:47.158 --> 38:50.161
-Yes, Your Honor.
-The defendant will please rise.

38:52.455 --> 38:53.914
Madam Foreperson, what say you?

38:53.998 --> 38:56.459
We find the defendant, Denny Crane...

38:57.585 --> 38:58.544
not guilty.

38:58.627 --> 39:00.546
(people murmuring)

39:01.797 --> 39:04.717
-Oh, thank God.
-Congratulations, Denny.

39:05.092 --> 39:07.970
Uh, could Your Honor find
as a matter of law that I am not gay?

39:09.055 --> 39:10.348
Denied!

39:10.973 --> 39:13.017
-(gavel pounds)
-Adjourned.

39:13.851 --> 39:15.311
ALAN: You must be deeply relieved.

39:15.394 --> 39:16.645
Oh, I could hug you.

39:17.271 --> 39:19.357
-But I might get arrested.
-Hug me anyway.

39:20.900 --> 39:22.193
-Mr. Crane?
-(camera shutter clicks)

39:26.322 --> 39:28.282
-REPORTER: Could we get a statement?
-(reporters clamoring)

39:28.366 --> 39:30.659
Not gay, not guilty.

39:38.876 --> 39:42.046
Tell me the truth. Wouldn't you hate it
if people thought you were gay?

39:44.590 --> 39:49.178
Well, I'd hate the idea of being perceived
as deceitful or dishonest.

39:50.346 --> 39:52.264
As for sexual orientation, I...

39:54.642 --> 39:56.936
Women are much less guarded
around gay men, Denny.

39:57.853 --> 40:00.022
You could endear yourself
as a bit of a Trojan horse

40:00.106 --> 40:01.690
before surprising them with your...

40:02.358 --> 40:03.651
Trojan.

40:04.735 --> 40:05.945
I never thought of that.

40:07.071 --> 40:09.698
This could be an advantage. (chuckles)

40:14.120 --> 40:15.913
Thank you, Alan.

40:16.831 --> 40:21.001
I'm not crazy about you lumping me
with that closet Democrat from Idaho,

40:21.085 --> 40:21.961
-but--
-(scoffs)

40:23.879 --> 40:24.922
Still, thank you.

40:26.715 --> 40:30.553
Can you believe the DA
tried to exploit us for being flamingos?

40:30.636 --> 40:32.388
Oh, ridiculous.

40:33.556 --> 40:35.433
Thank God he didn't find out
we like to dress up

40:35.516 --> 40:37.101
-as the Lennon Sisters.
-(chuckles)

40:38.644 --> 40:41.063
He actually tried
to shame us for our sleepovers.

40:41.313 --> 40:42.314
Bigot!

40:42.606 --> 40:44.233
Those homosexuals,

40:44.316 --> 40:47.153
can't stand the thought
of legitimate male bonding.

40:47.236 --> 40:48.904
-Where's the tolerance?
-Mmm.

40:49.697 --> 40:53.367
Oh, did you hear
Shirley went up against Bethany?

40:54.368 --> 40:55.911
-No.
-Uh-huh.

40:57.246 --> 40:58.289
Mmm.

40:58.372 --> 41:00.708
God, it's been so long
since I've had sex with a dwarf.

41:02.001 --> 41:02.835
Me, too.

41:05.379 --> 41:06.338
Me, too.

41:06.839 --> 41:08.466
It's the little things, Alan.

41:08.549 --> 41:09.967
(laughs)

41:10.050 --> 41:11.427
We gotta stop working so much.

41:11.510 --> 41:13.345
Maybe if you could stop getting arrested.

41:14.180 --> 41:15.139
I'm the problem?

41:15.222 --> 41:18.851
Well, you have been causing
a fair amount of trouble lately.

41:20.269 --> 41:21.103
(sighs)

41:21.937 --> 41:23.439
Do you think I've lived the evil life?

41:23.522 --> 41:24.857
(scoffs)

41:24.940 --> 41:27.610
I womanize, I drink, I break the law.

41:27.943 --> 41:31.155
And now, to be mistaken for a-a...

41:33.240 --> 41:36.952
Well, you get to be my age,
you worry about the afterlife...

41:38.370 --> 41:39.455
where you're heading.

41:41.916 --> 41:43.459
You ever think about those things?

41:46.003 --> 41:46.962
Sometimes.

41:48.297 --> 41:50.299
Then I remember what Mark Twain said.

41:50.382 --> 41:52.885
"You go to heaven for the climate,
but to hell for the company" so...

41:53.636 --> 41:55.346
(chuckles)
No matter what, in the end...

41:55.930 --> 41:56.931
We'll be together.

41:57.598 --> 42:00.809
-Indeed.
-Soul mates in hell. I love it.

42:01.143 --> 42:01.977
(Alan chuckles)

42:05.481 --> 42:07.399
Bet they have dwarves in hell.

42:07.858 --> 42:09.026
How could they not?

42:11.570 --> 42:13.614
Suddenly I'm less afraid of death.

42:15.491 --> 42:16.325
ALAN: There you go.

42:31.715 --> 42:32.883
NARRATOR: <i>Next on</i> Boston Legal...

42:32.967 --> 42:34.385
I'm considering going back to New York.

42:34.468 --> 42:36.929
Carl, come on.
This is just like any other firm.

42:37.012 --> 42:38.347
The things that go on here.

42:38.430 --> 42:40.474
The bailiff will take Mr. Shore
and Mr. Crane into custody

42:40.558 --> 42:42.643
for contempt of court and country!

42:42.726 --> 42:44.103
I'm gonna join the National Guard.

42:44.186 --> 42:45.771
I'm afraid neither of you can join.

42:45.854 --> 42:47.314
We want to shoot people.

42:47.398 --> 42:50.693
I can't figure out why you would sign on
for high profile cases.

42:50.776 --> 42:53.862
Just seems odd for somebody
who's got a fatwa against her.

42:53.946 --> 42:56.073
I am in big trouble, Grammy.

42:56.156 --> 42:58.409
Okay. Is it me,
or is that little thing hot?

42:58.492 --> 43:01.078
You're right, Shirley.
Just like any other firm.

43:03.330 --> 43:05.541
(theme music playing)
